		<h2 class="heading" id="productCreation">Creating Products</h2>
		<div class="content">
			<p>Click on 'Products' in the top menu.  Then click on 'New Product.'</p>
			<p>In the window that opens, enter some details about the product.  A name, weight, and price are required.  Click 'Create' and the product and its first variation will be created.</p>
			<p><b>When you first create a product, it will be active but <i>out of stock.</i> as noted by the label next to both the product and variation name.</b>  More on this later, but to stock the product immediately just click the 'Re-Stock All' button below the product image.</p>
		</div>
	</article>
	
	<hr>
	
	<article>
		<h2 class="heading" id="variantCreation">Creating Variants</h2>
		<div class="content">
			<p>Once you've created a product you might want to add a few variants.  If you aren't already on a product page, click on 'Products' in the top menu and click on a product, its name, or the 'details' button.  </p>
			<p>Below the product picture you can click the 'Add New Variant' button to bring up a new window.  There enter some details about the product variant and click 'Create.'  <b>Just like a newly created product, a variant will be initially out of stock.</b>  You can click "Re-Stock" under the corresponding variation you wish to restock.</p>
		</div>
	</article>
	
	<hr>
	
	<article>
		<h2 class="heading" id="productEdits">Editing Products and Variants</h2>
		<div class="content">
			<p>You can edit a product or variant by navigating to the product page.</p>
			<b> Editing Products</b>
			<p>Click on 'Edit Product Details.'</p><p>  There you can change the product's category, subcategory, and alternate names.</p>
			<b> Editing Variants</b>
			<p> For each variant you'll want to set a price/weight combination.  Prices and weights go hand in hand, so you can't enter one without entering the other.  To add one, just click "Add a Weight/Price" under the variant you wish to modify and enter a price and weight in the ensuing window.  You can select to enter it in ounces or pounds. </p>
			<b> Understanding Stock and 'Status'</b>
			<p>Both products and their variants have options to activate/deactivate and stock/unstock.  When you activate a product it becomes available to customers on your site.  On the products page you can deactivate a product, <b>which will deactivate all of the product's variants</b>  If a product is deactivated you'll see a button to 'activate' the product instead.  If you deactivate a variant, just that variant will be deactivated.</p>
			<p>Stock merely tells customers that the product or variant is in stock.  You can change this from the individual product pages.  Each variant can be "stocked" or "unstocked" by clicking on the button under the respective variant.  Also, you can 'unstock' or 'stock' <i>all</i> of a product's variants by clicking the "Unstock All" or "Stock All" button under a product on its page.</p>
			<b>Understanding Master Variants</b>
			<p>Each product, if active and stocked, has a master variant.  This is the variation that will appear first and 'represent' the product.  You can set a variant as 'Master' by clicking the green "Set As Master" button next to each variant.  </p>
			<p><b>Even if you don't explicitly set a variant to 'master', as long as a product has a variant that is stocked and active it will set a variant to display on the front end. </b></p>
			<p><b>Also, please note that there is no deletion of products.  You merely deactivate them.  The reasoning behind this is that deleting a product would remove any trace of that product in the system, which possibly could conflict with tracking of past orders, or future functionality that gives you feedback about what your customers/visitors have been browsing. </b></p>
		</div>
	</article>
	
