	<article>
		<h2 class="heading" id="orders">Keeping Track of Orders</h2>
		<div class="content">
			<p>Anytime a visitor adds items to his/her cart, clicks "checkout" and enters personal information, an order is created.  <b><i>At this point the order state is 'Unpaid.'</i></b>  Once a visitor enters payment information and pays the state becomes 'Paid.'  An order's state can change to 'Shipped' only if you mark it as so in the admin area.</p>
			<p>Click on "Orders" in the top navigation and you'll be taken to your order page.  Here you'll see the total money you've accepted as well as a link to your Stripe Account <i>more on that soon.</i></p>
			<p>Below that, you see a list of your orders that you can filter based on its state.  If an order is paid but not shipped you'll see a button that says "Mark as Shipped."  This is just so you can keep track of which orders you've shipped or that have been picked up.</p>
			<p><b>View more about an order, including shipping and customer information, by clicking "Show Order."</b></p>
			<p><i>All order have a unique 'uuid' (universal unique ID) that is generated.</i>  Feel free to use it on invoices, though its main purpose is to keep visitors from guessing others' order numbers.</p>
		</div>
	</article>
	
